	(1872,1814,'ENU0306',104,1,'神探福爾摩斯 （小說與電影）','Sherlock Holmes, Fiction and Film',4096,'','','H',2,56,'',0,'2','N',0,'1','',0,'','本部誠201',NULL,'一8-9',0,'',NULL,20,0.27,5,75,2,'This course intends to introduce to students selected canonical works of Sherlock Holmes short stories and novels. We will also watch film adaptations of Sherlock Holmes stories. The major issues we will discuss include, among others, London, East End, opium dens, sailors, adventure stories, crime fiction, modern medicine, forensics, and Darwinism. We will also screen such early silent films as Broken Blossoms, inspired by Sherlock Holmes and set in East End of London, and most recent Sherlock Holmes movies and BBC production of Sherlock Holmes set in the 21st century of Iphone, internet, GPA, blog and crime scenes.',0,26,26,0,0,0,0,0,0),
	(1873,1815,'ENU0317',104,1,'中國經典英譯精選','Selections from Chinese Classics in English Translation',4078,'','','H',3,56,'',0,'2','N',0,'1','◎限本系修習◎限大二大三大四修習',0,'','本部樸105',NULL,'三6-8',0,'',NULL,20,0.4,3,50,3,'The aim of the course is manifold: first, it hopes above all to acquaint students with wisdom passed down by the ancient saints and sages of China, in the hope that they can apply it to deal with their day-to-day encounter; second, it aims to improve students\' proficiency in both the English and the Chinese language; third, it attempts to enhance students\' abilities to appreciate and elaborate on the Chinese tradition in relation to the western cultural tradition and further acknowledge the strength of both cultures. The English textbook to be used Qunshu Zhiyao 360 (群書治要360) is a selection from a Chinese compilation <<群書治要>>. The book was decreed to be compiled by the emperor Taizong (599-649) of the Tang dynasty; it includes exerpts from 14,000 books and 89,000 scrolls of ancient writings, dating from the era of the Five Lengendary Emperors to the Jin dynasty. Along with the English translation, relevant materials from our time will be studied for putting into perspective both the ancient ideas and our ideas.',0,10,10,0,0,0,0,0,0),
	(1874,1816,'ENU0150',104,1,'英語教學概論','Introduction to TEFL',4097,'','1','H',2,56,'',1,'2','N',0,'','◎限本系修習◎限大二修習',0,'','本部正305',NULL,'四1-2',0,'',NULL,20,0.4,0,50,2,'Course Description: This is a one emester, 2 credit, mandatory course for English majors. The main objective of this course is to introduce you to theories and methods of teaching English to speakers of other languages. In this course, we will trace the historical development of second language teaching methods from grammar based curricula to present day interactive methods, where most of our focus will be placed. TESOL approaches and methods will be studied in their practical settings and in terms of their theoretical underpinnings. In addition to the theoretical focus, we will also discuss the practical aspects of teaching English as a foreign/second language. By the end of the course, you will be well-versed in applying major teaching methods that are currently being used in most EFL/ESL classrooms. teaching.',0,39,39,0,1,0,0,0,0),
	(1875,1817,'ENU0232',104,1,'文法與修辭（一）','Grammar & Rhetoric (I)',4098,'','1','H',2,56,'',0,'2','N',0,'','◎限本系修習◎限大二修習',0,'','本部正303',NULL,'二3-4',0,'',NULL,20,0.4,2,50,2,'This course will give an overview of the major features of English grammar. It will not cover all grammatical features in English, but rather aim at initiating independent thinking and research on the problematic areas of English grammar. You will become familiar with the intricacies of English grammar, particularly those that tend to be challenging to nonnative speakers. In this course you will learn to describe how English sentences are constructed and you will develop the skills necessary to analyze and explain English words, phrases and sentences, as well as learn the terminology to talk about them. In addition, you will learn about a corpus-based approach to studying vocabulary. Examining the use of words in natural contexts and different registers sheds light on our understanding of their true senses.',0,39,39,0,0,0,0,0,0),
	(1876,1818,'ENU0259',104,1,'語言學概論（一）','Introduction to Linguistics (I)',4099,'','1','H',2,56,'',1,'2','N',0,'','◎限本系修習◎限大二修習',0,'','本部誠305',NULL,'二1-2',0,'',NULL,20,0.4,2,50,2,'This course aims to familiarize the students enrolled with the fundamental concepts and the basic skills required for doing linguistic analysis. It is hoped that with these concepts and skills the students will be better equipped both for more advanced linguistics courses and as a competent English teacher.',0,47,47,0,6,0,0,0,0),
