	(1905,1847,'ENU6020',104,1,'當代世界文學（一）','Contemporary World Literature (I)',4081,'','','H',2,56,'',0,'3','N',0,'1','',0,'','本部正306',NULL,'二9-10',0,'',NULL,20,0.4,0,50,2,'有鑑於本系文學課程泰半偏重英美兩國，文學史講授也大多止於二十世紀初期，本課程將以當代非英語系國家文學為焦點，閱讀幾部經典著作，補強學生對世界文學的認知。課程目的不在於單純的文學賞析，而是冀望透過文學閱讀，鍛鍊學生對「可能性」的不平凡視角、看見文學書寫內的另類世界觀。課程選材橫跨多國、多文化，每位作家對歷史、政治、倫理、愛情、慾望、邪惡、救贖、死亡等主題都有特異（甚至異於常理）的處理觀點。本課程除了探討各觀點所提供的存有論與認識論外，並將深入分析各個作家的小說書寫理念、以及他們個別的寫作手法對世界文學的深遠影響。課程前半段並將系統性引介敘事學研究方法，深化學生的文學思辨能力。 本課程最終目的為拓展學生的人文視野。除了以當代世界文學為主要媒介，並將輔以相關主題的世界電影，開發學生對人文議題的敏銳度及討論興趣。',0,32,32,0,0,0,0,0,0),
	(1906,1848,'ENUE001',104,1,'英語教材教法（教）','Teaching Materials and Methods : English',4112,'','','H',2,56,'',1,'3','N',0,'1','◎限本系修習◎限大三大四修習',0,'','本部正302',NULL,'四1-2',0,'',NULL,10,0.2,0,50,2,'This is an introductory course that aims at helping students become familiar with current theories and practices in EFL teaching and learning. Students will be exposed to common approaches and practices in EFL through reading articles, viewing video-tapes, and doing hands-on projects. The focus of the first semester is on introducing ESL methods and approaches and the second semester will focus on techniques to teaching language skills and components.',0,35,35,0,2,0,0,0,0),
	(1907,1849,'ENU0013',104,1,'研究方法','Research Methods',4113,'A','1','H',2,56,'',1,'3','N',0,'','◎限本系修習◎限大三◎限甲班修習',0,'','本部正304',NULL,'四3-4',0,'',NULL,20,0.4,1,50,2,'In this course we will learn basic skills of doing research in literature and cultural studies: read literary, theoretical, and cinematic texts, find research topics, gather reference material, learn appropriate reference style, and write papers. In this current semester we take \"desire\" as the central topic of research. We\'ll watch films, read a play, and study critical essays, seeking in them ideas and questions for our discussion of the nature and mechanisms of desire: What, why, and how does one desire? Is our desire inborn or is it made? Who or what determines what we desire and how? What makes love possible (or inevitable) and in what way could an object be elevated to the status of a fetish? Moreover, how do gender, race, and culture play into the structure of desire? How does cinema (or other literary and cultural texts) foster or change the audience\'s desire? Questions like these and others will be asked through the semester. Participants are encouraged to come up with their own discussions and critical opinions based on their understanding of the texts selected. Along with these thinking and discussions, we will also learn basic MLA reference style, practice the skills of citation and documentation, and read paper samples.',0,20,20,0,5,0,0,0,0),
