	(1925,1867,'ENU0247',104,1,'討論與辯論（一）','Discussion & Debate (I)',4092,'A','1','H',2,56,'',1,'4','N',0,'','◎限本系修習◎限大四修習',0,'','本部正304',NULL,'二3-4',0,'',NULL,10,0.4,0,25,2,'本課旨在訓練培養學生參與英語討論及辯論之口語能力。在辯論的部分(秋季實施)，學生將修習基本邏輯思考技巧、英語辯論型式及策略、交叉質詢與反駁技巧和論述言談特色。課程進行方式主要為全班討論、小組報告討論，及實地模擬演練不同類型之小組討論與辯論。在討論的部分(春季實施)，學生將習得小組討論之目的，討論者之角色及如何策畫、參與評量不同類型之小組討論（如二人對談、圓桌論壇、小組座談、專題研討及公開討論）。學習評量包含學生個人及所屬小組之課堂表現及學生個人於課外小組討論時的準備與貢獻。 The course aims to cultivate students\' ability to use English to conduct a debate and a formal discussion. For English debate, which is conducted primarily in the fall semester, students will first acquire some fundamental critical thinking skills. They will then learn about debate format and structure, affirmative and negative case strategies, cross-examination techniques, and rebuttal skills. Once they are equipped with these debate basics, they will be asked to do at least two policy debates in class. For English discussion, which is conducted mostly in the spring semester, students will learn the purpose of discussion, the roles of discussants, and the ways of planning, participating in and evaluating different types of discussion, including dialogue, panel, symposium, forum, and round table. The reading materials are presented through either a brief lecture from the instructor followed by a Q&A session between the instructor and the class or group presentations done by the students. Students will be evaluated for their individual performance and their contributions to group assignments.',0,12,12,0,1,0,0,0,0),
