	(1935,1583,'ENM1051',104,1,'當代文學理論與文化研究','Contemporary Literary Theory & Cultural Studies',4117,'','','H',3,57,'',1,'','N',0,'1','',0,'','本部教室自排',NULL,'四2-4',0,'',NULL,20,0.4,5,50,3,'The purpose of this course is to introduce students to a range of texts from the fields of literary theory and cultural studies. Besides offering them some methodological co-ordinates for their own future research and training them in techniques of discussing and writing clearly about complex ideas, the course is designed to stimulate students\' critical thinking. In particular, it is hoped that they will learn to reflect sceptically on the dominant cultural values of their own society and educational culture as a result of their close reading of essays and other works that bring into focus some of the most egregious products of stupefaction issuing from the west.',0,10,10,0,0,0,0,0,0),
	(1936,1584,'ENM1057',104,1,'英文寫作與研究方法（一）','English Writing and Research Methods (I)',4118,'','','H',2,57,'',1,'','N',0,'','',0,'','本部教室自排',NULL,'一3-4',0,'',NULL,20,0.4,0,50,2,'The course is designed to enable students the following background knowledge and professional skills: (1) To introduce the learners to the concept of \' research\'; (2) To enable them to understand the stages of research; (3) To familiarize the learners to the procedures involved in research; (4) To introduce them to the conventions of research papers; (5) To familiarize them the techniques and conventions of research documentation.',0,7,7,0,0,0,0,0,0),
