	(2760,3081,'AHM0002',104,1,'中國繪畫史研究導論','Methodology in the History of Chinese Painting',4711,'','','H',3,110,'',0,'','N',0,'1','◎限碩一碩二碩三以上◎限博一博二博三博四博五以上修習',0,'','校外教室自排',NULL,'三7-9',0,'不開放上修',NULL,8,0.27,10,30,3,'本課程之主旨在介紹繪畫史研究的基本特性。希望透過重要繪畫史或是藝術史論著之閱讀，對藝術史做為一門學科所有具有的不同於其他的人文學科的特點有所闡發，同時針對中國繪畫史的特性作簡要的介紹與討論，並訓練學生能閱讀及判別研究論文之良窳。同時透過練習，能適切的運用工具書、參考書、電子資料等，以了解藝術史研究(尤其是中國繪畫史)、專業領域中可資運用的資源與將來可從事研究之方向。',0,6,6,0,0,0,0,0,0),
	(2761,3082,'AHM0020',104,1,'圖像學','Iconography',4712,'','','H',3,110,'',0,'','N',0,'1','◎限碩一碩二碩三以上◎限博一博二博三博四博五以上修習',0,'','校外教室自排',NULL,'一8-10',0,'不開放上修',NULL,8,0.27,10,30,3,'增進對圖像主題及內涵的認知。 培養對圖像的比較、分析與詮釋能力。 培養形塑、解決圖像相關議題的能力。 具備蒐集、研究與分析相關文獻史料的能力。 增進圖像學研究法的實際操作經驗。',0,12,12,0,0,0,0,0,0),
	(2762,3083,'AHM0045',104,1,'日治時期臺灣美術','Art of Taiwan in Japanese Colonial Period',4713,'','','H',3,110,'',0,'','N',0,'1','◎限碩一碩二碩三以上◎限博一博二博三博四博五以上修習',0,'','校外教室自排',NULL,'五3-5',0,'不開放上修',NULL,8,0.27,10,30,3,'1895至1945年，日本統治者主導殖民地台灣快速邁向近代化轉型，在此過程日本近代美術隨之引進。日本近代美術在此生根成長，並發展出具有台灣特色的美術，後續更影響戰後現代美術的發展，因此日治時期為台灣美術萌芽與發展的關鍵性階段，值得深入探究。本課程將以官方美術展覽會、美術家與作品為主軸，探討台灣近代美術風格的形成、作品圖像的社會文化意義，思索其與殖民現代性(colonial modernity)的關聯，並檢討各類型藝術的發展與限制，以及重要的議題研究。這門課亦培養學生研究台灣美術應具備的基本能力，包括作品分析、史料蒐尋與閱讀、田野調查，以及研究論著方法的省思等。',0,5,5,0,0,0,0,0,0),
	(2763,3084,'AHM0063',104,1,'東方藝術技法與材料應用','Techniques and Materials in Eastern Art',4714,'','','H',3,110,'',0,'','N',0,'','◎限碩一碩二碩三以上◎限博一博二博三博四博五以上修習',0,'','校外教室自排',NULL,'一3-5',0,'不開放上修',NULL,8,0.27,10,30,3,'本課程的設計在於幫助藝術史專業的研究生對於中國藝術的技巧方面，進行實務方面的理解，從實際體驗各種藝術品類的技巧實踐。',0,9,9,0,0,0,0,0,0),
	(2764,3085,'AHM0081',104,1,'中國藝術史傳統文獻研究導論','Introduction to Traditional Documentary Sources in Chinese Art',4715,'','','H',3,110,'',0,'','N',0,'1','◎限碩一碩二碩三以上◎限博一博二博三博四博五以上修習',0,'','校外教室自排',NULL,'一3-5',0,'不開放上修',NULL,8,0.27,10,30,3,'本課程為東方藝術史組必選課程之一，將帶領學生透過個案討論與實例操作熟悉中國藝術史的傳統文獻及其用處，希望能對學生從事專題研究有所俾益。我們將檢視傳統書畫著錄、藝術理論、筆記小說與清宮檔案等，並討論這些文獻資料與藝術品實物的關係。此外，此課程也將帶領學生熟悉各種傳統文獻、檔案的電子資料庫。',0,3,3,0,0,0,0,0,0),
	(2765,3086,'AHM0108',104,1,'中國繪畫中的圖像與文本專題研究','Special Topics on Image and Texts in Chinese Painting',4716,'','','H',3,110,'',0,'','N',0,'1','◎限碩一碩二碩三以上◎限博一博二博三博四博五以上修習',0,'','校外教室自排',NULL,'四3-5',0,'不開放上修',NULL,8,0.27,10,30,3,'從一開始，中國畫便具有教化之功能，因而承載著某些特定的意義，畫作被視為特定文本或文意的演譯，使人易於接受，產生共鳴，進而達成其教化或是宣示政令之目的，這是公領域的藝文創作。在私領域中，圖像也被用來詮釋個人的意圖，尤其是隱士圖像以及相關於隱居地圖文的創作，或隱諱或突顯的傳達出隱者的心志。至於中國文學史上某些著名的文學作品，更是一再的為人圖而繪之，圖像則往往在原有文本之外又透露其他的訊息。如何察覺這些訊息？如何讀出畫外之意？因著文本的演變、時代風尚與需求之變易、繪畫功能的不同、創作者注重點之轉換，在在都對圖像與文本之關係造成影響，而這些錯綜複雜的圖文關係，正是本課程所關心的焦點。',0,4,4,0,0,0,0,0,0),
	(2766,3087,'AHM0116',104,1,'建築史研究導論','Introduction to Art-Historical Research for Architecture',4717,'','','H',3,110,'',1,'','N',0,'1','◎限碩一碩二碩三以上◎限博一博二博三博四博五以上修習',0,'','校外教室自排',NULL,'二7-9',0,'不開放上修',NULL,8,0.27,10,30,3,'The objective of the seminar is to provide an in-depth introduction to architectural history. It is the aim to present a compact overview of the classical research fields and methods as well as a summary of western history of architecture. On the basis of selected examples, students practice description and analysis methods of architectural research to enable them to study buildings independently. They should gain knowledge and develop judgment in order to evaluate autonomously scientific points of view. Furthermore, they learn to use bibliographic aids on the history of architecture and get skills of writing research papers.',0,3,3,0,0,0,0,0,0),
	(2767,3088,'AHM0143',104,1,'繪畫與電影專題研究：畫布與銀幕之間','Special Topics on Painting and Film: between the Canvas and the Movie Screen',4718,'','','H',3,110,'',1,'','N',0,'1','◎限碩一碩二碩三以上◎限博一博二博三博四博五以上修習',0,'','校外教室自排',NULL,'二3-5',0,'不開放上修',NULL,8,0.27,10,30,3,'Painting has been for a long time the privileged medium for transcribing reality and inventing fictions, but the inventions of the Frères Lumière and Thomas Edison in 1895 opened new perspectives. This course attempts to show the different relationships between painting and cinema from their fundamental difference to their intimate similitude. As the filiation between the painter Pierre-Auguste Renoir and his son the filmmaker illustrates, we do not find in the movies of Jean Renoir an imitation of the art of painting, but similarities and echoes. I. Several points of views will be proposed. First, there is a need to outline the new theoretical interest for cinema in art history. We notice that an increasing numbers of studies are now dedicated to film and art. It forces us to reconsider both mediums under a new light. For example it is now impossible not to take into account the works of Impressionism and their quest of instantaneity and movement without the context of the experimentations of Marey and Muybridge. The principles of series which appear for example in Degas\' Dancers and Nudes, and especially in Monet\'s Railway Stations, Poplars, Cathedrals and Ricks are connected with the cinematic experimentations of that time, too. II. Secondly, it is helpful to consider cinema under the heritage of painting, which constructed the western imaginary during several centuries. In this respect it appears that the multiple references with painting made in film seem to legitimate the respectability of cinema. In quoting such a prestigious medium as painting, directors want to demonstrate their legitimacy as authors: thus their movies cannot be considered only as a means of entertainment. This strategy appears with the films of the generation of Fritz Lang and Alfred Hitchcock and we will see how to analyze this heritage perpetuated in the 60\'s by Michelangelo Antonioni and the French Nouvelle Vague or today by Peter Greenaway and David Lynch. III. Finally it will be fruitful to assess the importance of films in the art of the 20th and 21st centuries. From the beginning cinema has been the vector of a new aesthetic, which has deeply impressed the artists. We can follow the influence of the first westerns and gangster movies (respectively Porter\'s The Great Train Robbery, 1903; Louis Feuillade\'sFantômas, 1913) on Dada and the Surrealists for example. The popular imagery of actors and films nourished Pop Art in the USA and its European counterpart during the 60\'s, while contemporary artists such as Cindy Sherman, Jeff Wall, Stan Douglas or Pierre Huyghe are still evoking and interrogating film imagery through their works.',0,2,2,0,0,0,0,0,0),
	(2768,3089,'AHM0147',104,1,'清宮繪畫專題研究','Special Topics on Court Paintings of the Qing Dynasty',4719,'','','H',3,110,'',0,'','N',0,'1','◎限碩一碩二碩三以上◎限博一博二博三博四博五以上修習',0,'','校外教室自排',NULL,'二7-9',0,'不開放上修',NULL,8,0.27,10,30,3,'近年來關於清宮藝術的研究突飛猛進，因為各博物館藏品（尤其是中國的博物館）與清宮檔案的開放與出版，多種研究成果陸續出現，也造成近年來清宮藝術的研究成為中國藝術史研究的顯學。本課程希望能帶領學生瞭解清宮繪畫，接觸最新的研究成果，並學習如何進行清宮繪畫的研究，包括如何使用檔案。',0,3,3,0,0,0,0,0,0),
	(2769,3090,'AHM0181',104,1,'巴洛克建築','Baroque Architecture',4717,'','','H',3,110,'',1,'','N',0,'1','◎限碩一碩二碩三以上◎限博一博二博三博四博五以上修習',0,'','校外教室自排',NULL,'三7-9',0,'不開放上修',NULL,8,0.27,10,30,3,'The educational objective of this course is to impart the scientific base of Baroque architecture in Europe. The course will provide an introduction, focusing initially the style\'s foundations in Italian Late Renaissance and Mannerism, and analyzing then works of the period\'s main protagonists, Giacomo Barozzi da Vignola (1507-73) and Giacomo della Porta (c. 1532-1602) with their designs for the mother church of the Jesuit order, Il Gesù in Rome, as well as Gian Lorenzo Bernini (1598-1680) and Francesco Borromini (1599-1667). It will be analyzed how the dogmatic thoughts of the Counter-Reformation influenced the art of building and determined the structures\' form and content. Subsequently, we shall consider the spreading of Baroque style all over Europe, taking into account the various important cultural centers, and especially France, southern Germany and Austria. In the focus will be religious as well as secular works. Students are expected to be capable of analyzing independently the buildings using the correct terminology. In interpreting and discussing essential texts on the topic, they should acquire a problem-based competence to use established and appropriate methodological analysis and are expected to be capable of working autonomously on scientific papers on architectural topics.',0,2,2,0,0,0,0,0,0),
	(2770,3091,'AHM0191',104,1,'中國陶瓷史','Ancient Chinese Porcelain',4714,'','','H',3,110,'',0,'','N',0,'1','◎限碩一碩二碩三以上◎限博一博二博三博四博五以上修習',0,'','校外教室自排',NULL,'一8-10',0,'不開放上修',NULL,8,0.27,10,30,3,'培養學生掌握中國陶瓷藝術史的基本知識，並學習從美學、材料、技術、政治、人文信仰與經濟等等各方面切入，進行陶瓷藝術史的研究。培養學生瞭解從新石器時代、夏商周、秦漢等朝代一直到清代，各個時代的陶瓷風格，包括技術、材料與花紋裝飾等等特色的熟悉，並對陶瓷在當時所扮演的社會階級、生活功能、商業貿易、文化交流等等的理解。',0,9,9,0,0,0,0,0,0),
	(2771,3092,'AHM0217',104,1,'近代日本美術史研究','Art History of Modern Japan',4711,'','','H',3,110,'',0,'','N',0,'1','◎限碩一碩二碩三以上◎限博一博二博三博四博五以上修習',0,'','校外教室自排',NULL,'四7-9',0,'不開放上修',NULL,8,0.27,10,30,3,'日本美術史的發展自19世紀中期起，無論從內在進行創作的思考方式、媒材，到外在建立美術的體制、教育、展覽會等等，均產生巨大的變化，使這段歷史發展饒富趣味，至今累積豐碩且多面的研究成果。本課程以日本明治到昭和戰前發展為序，聚焦於具代表性的美術事件、運動，與畫家等等，進行探討。',0,4,4,0,0,0,0,0,0),
	(2772,3093,'AHM0221',104,1,'二十世紀下半視覺藝術','Visual Arts in the Second Half of the 20th Century',4718,'','','H',3,110,'',1,'','N',0,'1','◎限碩一碩二碩三以上◎限博一博二博三博四博五以上修習',0,'','校外教室自排',NULL,'三3-5',0,'不開放上修',NULL,8,0.27,10,30,3,'The arts of the immediate post-war can be defined both in the West and in Japan by a dynamic of transgression that was provocative, violent, and also festive. This spirit and revivifying ardour that characterized the artistic creation in both aforementioned areas is also illustrated by common references rooted in neo-primitivism. A specific attention will be paid on the artistic production of the 1950s and 1960s. The attitudes and new forms of creation that took place during this period in Japan, Europe and the United States will be compared their impact on the next generations will be analysed critically.The multiplication of attitudes and artistic mixings of diverse origins that have been taking place since WWII needs and in-depth analysis. The course will provide tools to understand the different stakes related to the period analyzed. Divided in two parts, the course will on the one hand describe the different postures and traits that have defined the decades of creation following WWII. It will on the other hand comment through concrete case studies the links between the artistic creation and the larger realm of visual culture of this period marked by the emergence of television and new media. Visits to institutions hosting and promoting the art that has developed during the second half of the 20th century will be scheduled according to the calendar of events taking place during the semester.',0,3,3,0,0,0,0,0,0),
