	(3473,1411,'IWM0056',104,1,'國際性非營利組織人力資源發展研究','Studies in Human Resources Development for International Nonprofit Organizations',5130,'','','H',3,146,'',1,'2','N',0,'1','',0,'','本部教室自排',NULL,'二A-C',0,'',NULL,20,0.4,6,50,3,'This course uses a project-oriented approach and provides an introduction to the fundamental value questions about human resource practice in nonprofit sectors, also including educational, governmental, and non-governmental organizations. Each student will conduct a research project (e.g. thesis, conference paper, or other publications) that involves human resource issues in nonprofit, educational, and governmental organizations. Students will receive instruction individually with regard to their research projects. Through the course readings, discussion, and project implementation, students will have the opportunity to learn how to study human resource issues in nonprofit, educational, governmental, and nongovernmental sectors.',0,11,11,0,0,0,0,0,0),
	(3474,1412,'IWM0059',104,1,'中小企業人力資源專題研究','Special Topics on Human Resources for Small Business',5124,'','','H',3,146,'',1,'2','N',0,'1','◎限碩一碩二碩三以上◎限博一博二博三博四博五以上修習',0,'','本部教室自排',NULL,'五6-8',0,'不開放上修',NULL,20,0.4,0,50,3,'經濟發展的自由化、全球化已是國際經濟的脈動與趨勢，全球化經濟將產業結構進一步調整，促使中小企業必須努力提升產品及服務之附加價值。因此，本課程主要目的在於使學員瞭解中小企業所面臨的內外環境，以及其對於人力資源策略以及實務運作的影響。',0,6,6,0,0,0,0,0,0),
