	(3912,2037,'EMM0092',104,1,'音樂與社會學','Music and Sociology',5313,'','','H',2,155,'',1,'','N',0,'1','',0,'','本部教室自排',NULL,'二3-4',0,'',NULL,5,0.25,6,20,2,'This course will provide a graduate-level introduction to the most significant theoretical ideas and problems related to the study of music from a sociological perspective. The course will cover a variety of genres and music of different cultures, together with theoretical approaches from a variety of perspectives. Students will read and discuss some of the important literature in this field, and conduct their own research for class presentation and the final essay. The course will be taught in a seminar format, with discussions and group work on case-study exercises. Some weeks may include short introductory lectures. Readings will be primarily in English, but there will be scope for inclusion of some Chinese-language scholarly literature in discussion. Assessment will be submitted in English.',0,16,16,0,0,0,0,0,0),
	(3913,2379,'PAU0003',104,1,'表演鑑賞','Appreciation of Performing Arts',5320,'','','H',2,156,'',0,'','N',0,'','',0,'','本部誠204',NULL,'三9-10',0,'',NULL,20,0.4,2,50,2,'本課程以舞蹈、音樂、戲劇等之主要表演藝術經典名作，為主要欣賞教材。並以目前國內之重要表演藝術演出，為現場之賞析教材。且鼓勵學生參與國內外重要相關之大師講座，以大師之智慧、經驗與風範，作為學習之助力。',0,49,49,0,8,0,0,0,0),
